{
  "stem": "942.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And several months later, which was March of 1939, Czechoslovakia ceased to exist.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Nazis invaded Bohemia, Moravia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And part of Slovakia became an autonomous country under Cardinal Tiso, who was a Nazi sympathizer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this is where my maternal grandmother and my uncles and several uncles and cousins remained in Slovakia, and we became Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so this was March, '39.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were getting ourselves prepared for these Hungarian troops.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I know that it was a fearful time because we were so familiar with the Czech troops.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know we lived right near the border.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And many of these border guards, they used to come and drink in my father's place, and, you know, he was very friendly with everybody.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember that he had a rule that whenever these border guards came to drink, they had to take their pistols out, and they had to put it in a [INAUDIBLE] in a drawer.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I remember one day opening a drawer and it was full of pistols.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You know, and as a child, I thought I'm going to play cowboys.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I had all my friends come down and have a look at this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You know, I was sort of showing off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And these border guards and the Czechs were-- they were like dressed, you know, properly, you know, and they were very well trained.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we had no-- I had no problem with the Hungarians coming in because I spoke Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I remember my grandfather, who was an officer in the cavalry in the First World War-- and he was in Franz Joseph's Army-- in fact, many people, including my grandfather, had a beard and these sideburns just like Franz Joseph had.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he was taking all his medals out that he received on this Russian front.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
